post_cb({"bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_31341917_31341955_0": {"length": 42, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 110}}, "n3337": {"so_31341917_31341955_0": {"length": 42, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 105}}, "n4659": {"so_31341917_31341955_0": {"length": 42, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 114}}}, "31341917": {"ViewCount": "729", "Body": "<p>You can forward declare a template inner class inside a normal class, and use the defined type as any other forward declared type.</p>\n<pre><code>class Outer {\n    template &lt;int N&gt; class Inner;\n    typedef Inner&lt;0&gt; Inner0;\n    Inner0* f();\n};\n\ntemplate&lt;int N&gt;\nclass Outer::Inner {};\n</code></pre>\n<p>Now if Outer is itself a template class, is there a way to keep the declaration of Inner outside the declaration of Outer ? Something like :</p>\n<pre><code>template&lt;typename T&gt;\nclass Outer {\n    template &lt;int N&gt; class Inner;\n    typedef Inner&lt;0&gt; Inner0;\n    Inner0* f();\n};\n\ntemplate&lt;typename T, int N&gt; //This won't work\nclass Outer&lt;T&gt;::Inner {};\n</code></pre>\n<p>Is there a correct syntax to declare Outer with the right template parameters ?</p>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "31341955", "Title": "Forward declaration of template class nested inside template class", "CreationDate": "2015-07-10T13:23:30.057", "Id": "31341917", "CommentCount": "0", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastActivityDate": "2015-07-10T13:36:34.080", "Score": "5", "OwnerUserId": "746547", "Tags": "<c++><templates><nested>", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "31341955": {"Id": "31341955", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>Try the following</p>\n<pre><code>template&lt;typename T&gt;\ntemplate &lt;int N&gt;\nclass Outer&lt;T&gt;::Inner {};\n</code></pre>\n<p>According to the C++ Standard (14.5.2 Member templates)</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_31341917_31341955_0\">1 A template can be declared within a class or class template; such a\n  template is called a member template. A member template can be defined\n  within or outside its class definition or class template definition. <strong>A\n  member template of a class template that is defined outside of its\n  class template definition shall be specified with the\n  template-parameters of the class template followed by the\n  template-parameters of the member template.</strong></p>\n</blockquote>\n", "LastEditorUserId": "2877241", "LastActivityDate": "2015-07-10T13:36:34.080", "Score": "7", "CreationDate": "2015-07-10T13:24:52.633", "ParentId": "31341917", "CommentCount": "2", "OwnerUserId": "2877241", "LastEditDate": "2015-07-10T13:36:34.080"}});